@node misc "Fix560 documentation"

@{fg highlight}@{b}Miscellanous information@{fg text}@{ub}

  Fix560 has been tested on five different Amigas and four different 560 dpi
mouses, and on every one of them Fix560 worked and was of help, so I think
that it is safe to say that Fix560 really works :) It didn't crash the
machines either, as you probably thought... :)

The machines on which Fix560 was tested were:

- A1200, 060/50, OS3.0
- A1200, 030/50, OS3.0 (two of these)
- A4000, 040/30, OS3.1
- A1200, 060/50, OS3.0+WB3.1

Unfortunately, we had only Wizard's 3-button 560dpi mouses, so Fix560 hasn't
been tested on any other mouses, but why should they work any better without
Fix560?-) If you have some other kind of 560dpi mouse, then tell me about it
@{b}when@{ub} you mail me, and also tell me if Fix560 helped anything :)

@{fg highlight}@{b}The betatesters@{fg text}@{ub}

List of betatesters: Olli-P. Kaikuaho
                     Timo Sievänen
                     Simo Koivukoski

Thank you very much; I couldn't have published Fix560 if you hadn't told me
that it works! :)

If you suddenly feel the urge to become a betatester for future versions,
contact @{"me" link author} :)

